<blockquote>
  <p>Binding pocket</p>
</blockquote>

<font><p>Left: Surface representation of the binding pocket of the <i>Lactococcus lactis</i> <i>yybP-ykoY</i> manganese riboswitch generated from PDB ID: 4Y1I at 2.85 √Ö resolution. The manganese ion is labeled in red. Right: The metal coordination scheme. Mg<sup>2+</sup> is coordinated octahedrally by five backbone phosphates and a water. The Mn<sup>2+</sup> contains five backbone phosphates and the N7 of A41. N6 of A41 also makes a H-bond to the phosphate of U39<sup>[<a href="#ref3">3</a>]</sup>.</p></font>
<table class="table table-bordered" style="table-layout:fixed;width:1000px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;"><tr>
<td style="text-align:center;padding-bottom: 0px;padding-left: 0px;padding-top: 0px;padding-right: 0px"><img src="/images/binding_pockets/yybP-ykoY_manganese_riboswitch_binding_pockets1.svg" alt="drawing" style="width:500px" px="" /></td>
<td style="text-align:center;padding-bottom: 0px;padding-left: 0px;padding-top: 0px;padding-right: 0px"><img src="/images/binding_pockets/yybP-ykoY_manganese_riboswitch_binding_pockets2.svg" alt="drawing" style="width:500px" px="" /></td>
</tr>
